The '''Zentrum für Astronomie der Universität Heidelberg''' (Center for Astronomy of [[Heidelberg University]]) in [[Heidelberg|Heidelberg, Germany]], founded in 2005, is an association of three, formerly state-run research institutes: the [[Astronomisches Rechen-Institut]], the [[Institute of Theoretical Astrophysics (University of Heidelberg)|Institut für Theoretische Astrophysik]] (Institute for Theoretical Astrophysics) and the [[Landessternwarte Heidelberg-Königstuhl]] (Heidelberg-Königstuhl State Observatory).

